{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"We're going to talk -- my -- a new lecture, just"},{"time":1000,"text":"for TED -- and I'm going show you some illusions"},{"time":4000,"text":"that we've created for TED, and I'm going to try"},{"time":7000,"text":"to relate this to happiness. What I was thinking"},{"time":9000,"text":"about with happiness is, what gives happiness --"},{"time":12000,"text":"or happiness, which I equate with joy in my"},{"time":16000,"text":"particular area, and I think there's something very"},{"time":18000,"text":"fundamental. And I was thinking about this. And"},{"time":22000,"text":"it's in terms of both illusions and movies that we"},{"time":26000,"text":"go see and jokes and magic shows is that there's"},{"time":30000,"text":"something about these things where our"},{"time":32000,"text":"expectations are violated in some sort of pleasing"},{"time":36000,"text":"way. You go see a movie. And it has an unexpected"},{"time":39000,"text":"twist -- something that you didn't expect -- and"},{"time":42000,"text":"you find a joyful experience. You look at those"},{"time":45000,"text":"sort of illusions in my book and it's not as what"},{"time":48000,"text":"you'd expect. And there's something joyful about"},{"time":50000,"text":"it. And it's the same thing with jokes and all"},{"time":53000,"text":"these sorts of things. So, what I'm going to try"},{"time":56000,"text":"and do in my lecture is go a little bit further"},{"time":59000,"text":"and see if I can violate your expectations in a"},{"time":62000,"text":"pleasing way. I mean, sometimes expectations that"},{"time":65000,"text":"are violated are not pleasant, but I'm going to try"},{"time":67000,"text":"to do it in a pleasant way, in a very primal way,"},{"time":70000,"text":"so I can make the audience here happy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72000,"text":"So I'm going to show you some ways that we can"},{"time":75000,"text":"violate your expectations. First of all, I want to"},{"time":78000,"text":"show you the particular illusion here. I want you"},{"time":81000,"text":"first of all when it pops up on the screen to"},{"time":84000,"text":"notice that the two holes are perpendicular to"},{"time":86000,"text":"each other. These are all perceptual tricks. These"},{"time":90000,"text":"are real objects that I'm going to show you. Now"},{"time":101000,"text":"I'm going to show you how it is done. I've looped"},{"time":104000,"text":"the film here so you can get a very interesting"},{"time":106000,"text":"experience. I want you to see how this illusion is"},{"time":109000,"text":"constructed, and it's going to rotate so you see"},{"time":112000,"text":"that it's inside out. Now watch, as it rotates"},{"time":115000,"text":"back, how quickly your perception snaps. OK now."},{"time":121000,"text":"Watch it as it rotates back again. And this is a very"},{"time":124000,"text":"bright audience, all right? See if you can stop it"},{"time":127000,"text":"from happening, even though you know 100 percent it's"},{"time":130000,"text":"true that -- bam! You can't undo it. What does"},{"time":135000,"text":"that tell you about yourselves? We're going to do"},{"time":139000,"text":"it again. No doubt about it. See if you can stop"},{"time":142000,"text":"it from happening. No. It's difficult."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149000,"text":"And we can violate your expectations in a whole"},{"time":152000,"text":"variety of ways about representation, about shape,"},{"time":155000,"text":"about color and so forth and it's very primal. And"},{"time":158000,"text":"it's an interesting question to ponder, why these"},{"time":161000,"text":"things -- we find these things joyful. Why would"},{"time":165000,"text":"we find them joyful? So, here's something that"},{"time":168000,"text":"Lionel did a while ago. I like these sort of"},{"time":170000,"text":"little things like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174000,"text":"Again, this is not an optical trick. This is what"},{"time":177000,"text":"you would see. In other words, it's not a camera"},{"time":197000,"text":"cut. It's a perceptual trick."},{"time":210000,"text":"OK. We can violate your expectations about"},{"time":212000,"text":"shape."},{"time":231000,"text":"We can violate your expectations on representation"},{"time":235000,"text":"-- what an image represents. What do you see here?"},{"time":240000,"text":"How many of you here see dolphins? Raise your hand"},{"time":247000,"text":"if you see dolphins. OK, those people who raised"},{"time":251000,"text":"their hands, afterwards, the rest of the audience,"},{"time":253000,"text":"go talk to them, all right? Actually, this is the"},{"time":257000,"text":"best example of priming by experience that I know."},{"time":261000,"text":"If you are a child under the age of 10 who"},{"time":265000,"text":"haven't been ruined yet, you will look at this"},{"time":268000,"text":"image and see dolphins. Now, some of you adults"},{"time":272000,"text":"here are saying, \"What dolphins? What dolphins?\""},{"time":274000,"text":"But in fact, if you reversed the figure ground --"},{"time":277000,"text":"in other words, the dark areas here -- I forgot to"},{"time":280000,"text":"ask for a pointer -- but if you reverse it, you'll"},{"time":282000,"text":"see a whole series of little dolphins. By the way,"},{"time":285000,"text":"if you're also a student at CalTech -- they also"},{"time":288000,"text":"tend to just see the dolphins. It's based on"},{"time":291000,"text":"experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295000,"text":"Now, something like this can be used because this"},{"time":298000,"text":"is after all talk about design, too. This was"},{"time":300000,"text":"done by Saatchi and Saatchi, and they actually got"},{"time":303000,"text":"away with this ad in Australia. So, if you look at"},{"time":306000,"text":"this ad for beer, all those people are in sort of"},{"time":311000,"text":"provocative positions. But they got it passed, and"},{"time":314000,"text":"actually won the Clio awards, so it's funny how you can do"},{"time":318000,"text":"these things."},{"time":319000,"text":"Remember that sort of, um. This is the joke I did"},{"time":327000,"text":"when the Florida ballot was going around. You"},{"time":331000,"text":"know, count the dots for Gore; count the dots for"},{"time":333000,"text":"Bush; count 'em again ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338000,"text":"You can violate your expectations about"},{"time":341000,"text":"experience. Here is an outside water fountain that"},{"time":348000,"text":"I created with some friends of mine, but you can"},{"time":350000,"text":"stop the water in drops and -- actually make all"},{"time":353000,"text":"the drops levitate. This is something we're"},{"time":359000,"text":"building for, you know, amusement parks and that"},{"time":361000,"text":"kind of stuff."},{"time":362000,"text":"Now let's take a static image. Can you see this?"},{"time":366000,"text":"Do you see the middle section moving down and the"},{"time":369000,"text":"outer sections moving up? It's completely static."},{"time":373000,"text":"It's a static image. How many people see this"},{"time":375000,"text":"illusion? It's completely static."},{"time":381000,"text":"Right. Now, when -- it's interesting that when we"},{"time":384000,"text":"look at an image we see, you know, color, depth,"},{"time":388000,"text":"texture. And you can look at this whole scene and"},{"time":391000,"text":"analyze it. You can see the woman is in closer than"},{"time":394000,"text":"the wall and so forth. But the whole thing is"},{"time":396000,"text":"actually flat. It's painted. It's trompe l'oeil."},{"time":401000,"text":"And it was such a good trompe l'oeil that people"},{"time":403000,"text":"got irritated when they tried to talk to the"},{"time":405000,"text":"woman and she wouldn't respond."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"Now, you can make design mistakes. Like this"},{"time":414000,"text":"building in New York. So that when you see it from"},{"time":420000,"text":"this side, it looks like the balconies tilt up,"},{"time":423000,"text":"and when you walk around to the other side it"},{"time":425000,"text":"looks like the balconies go down. So there are"},{"time":430000,"text":"cases where you have mistakes in design that"},{"time":432000,"text":"incorporate illusions."},{"time":433000,"text":"Or, you take this particular un-retouched"},{"time":436000,"text":"photograph. Now, interestingly enough, I get a lot"},{"time":444000,"text":"of emails from people who say, \"Is there any"},{"time":446000,"text":"perceptual difference between males and females?\""},{"time":451000,"text":"And I really say, \"No.\" I mean, women can navigate"},{"time":453000,"text":"through the world just as well as males can -- and"},{"time":456000,"text":"why wouldn't they? However, this is the one"},{"time":458000,"text":"illusion that women can consistently do better"},{"time":461000,"text":"than males: in matching which head because they"},{"time":464000,"text":"rely on fashion cues. They can match the hat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470000,"text":"Okay, now getting to a part -- I want to show"},{"time":472000,"text":"design in illusions. I believe that the first"},{"time":475000,"text":"example of illusions being used purposely was by"},{"time":480000,"text":"da Vinci in this anamorphic image of an eye. So"},{"time":486000,"text":"that when you saw from one little angle was like"},{"time":489000,"text":"this. And this little technique got popular in the"},{"time":492000,"text":"16th century and the 17th century to disguise"},{"time":495000,"text":"hidden meanings, where you could flip the image and"},{"time":498000,"text":"see it from one little point of view like this."},{"time":503000,"text":"But these are early incorporations of illusions"},{"time":506000,"text":"brought to -- sort of high point with Hans"},{"time":508000,"text":"Holbein's \"Ambassadors.\" And Hans Holbein worked"},{"time":511000,"text":"for Henry VIII. This was hung on a wall where you"},{"time":515000,"text":"could walk down from the stair and you can see"},{"time":517000,"text":"this hidden skull."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521000,"text":"All right, now I'm going to show you some"},{"time":524000,"text":"designers who work with illusions to give that"},{"time":526000,"text":"element of surprise. One of my favorites is Scott"},{"time":529000,"text":"Kim. I worked with Scott to create some illusions"},{"time":533000,"text":"for TED that I hope you will enjoy. We have one"},{"time":538000,"text":"here on TED and happiness."},{"time":556000,"text":"OK now. Arthur [Ganson] hasn't talked yet, but his is"},{"time":559000,"text":"going to be a delightful talk and he has some of"},{"time":562000,"text":"his really fantastic machines outside. And so, we"},{"time":569000,"text":"-- Scott created this wonderful tribute to Arthur"},{"time":572000,"text":"Ganson."}]},{"cues":[{"time":584000,"text":"Well, there's analog and digital. Thought that"},{"time":592000,"text":"was appropriate here."},{"time":598000,"text":"And figure goes to ground."},{"time":613000,"text":"And for the musicians."},{"time":634000,"text":"And of course, since happiness -- we want \"joy to the"},{"time":636000,"text":"world.\""},{"time":646000,"text":"Now, another great designer -- he's very well"},{"time":648000,"text":"known in Japan -- Shigeo Fukuda. And he just"},{"time":653000,"text":"builds some fantastic things. This is simply"},{"time":655000,"text":"amazing. This is a pile of junk that when you view"},{"time":662000,"text":"it from one particular angle, you see its"},{"time":671000,"text":"reflection in the mirror as a perfect piano."},{"time":689000,"text":"Pianist transforms to violinist."},{"time":702000,"text":"This is really wild. This assemblage of forks,"},{"time":708000,"text":"knives and spoons and various cutlery, welded"},{"time":711000,"text":"together. It gives a shadow of a motorcycle. You learn"},{"time":724000,"text":"something in the sort of thing that I do, which"},{"time":727000,"text":"is there are people out there with a lot of time"},{"time":729000,"text":"on their hands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734000,"text":"Ken Knowlton does wonderful composite images, like"},{"time":740000,"text":"creating Jacques Cousteau out of seashells --"},{"time":742000,"text":"un-retouched seashells, but just by rearranging"},{"time":744000,"text":"them. He did Einstein out of dice because, after"},{"time":748000,"text":"all, Einstein said, \"God does not play dice with"},{"time":751000,"text":"the universe.\" Bert Herzog out of un-retouched"},{"time":756000,"text":"keyboards. Will Shortz, crossword puzzle. John"},{"time":761000,"text":"Cederquist does these wonderful trompe l'oeil"},{"time":765000,"text":"cabinets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767000,"text":"Now, I'm going to skip ahead since I'm sort of running"},{"time":769000,"text":"[behind]. I want to show you quickly what I've"},{"time":772000,"text":"created, some new type of illusions. I've done"},{"time":777000,"text":"something with taking the Pixar-type illusions. So"},{"time":781000,"text":"you see these kids the same size here, running"},{"time":785000,"text":"down the hall. The two table tops of the same size."},{"time":788000,"text":"They're looking out two directions at once. You"},{"time":792000,"text":"have a larger piece fitting in with a smaller. And"},{"time":799000,"text":"that's something for you to think about, all"},{"time":801000,"text":"right? So you see larger pieces fitting in within"},{"time":803000,"text":"smaller pieces here. Does everyone see that? Which"},{"time":807000,"text":"is impossible. You can see the two kids are"},{"time":812000,"text":"looking out simultaneously out of two different"},{"time":814000,"text":"directions at once. Now can you believe these two"},{"time":821000,"text":"table tops are the same size and shape? They are."},{"time":825000,"text":"So, if you measured them, they would be. And as I say,"},{"time":831000,"text":"those two figures are identical in size and shape."},{"time":837000,"text":"And it's interesting, by doing this in this sort"},{"time":841000,"text":"of rendered fashion, how much stronger the"},{"time":844000,"text":"illusions are. Any case, I hope this has brought"},{"time":846000,"text":"you a little joy and happiness, and if you're"},{"time":848000,"text":"interested in seeing more cool effects, see me"},{"time":851000,"text":"outside. I'd be happy to show you lots of things."}]}]}